  "headline": "Array Data Structure",
  "description": "An array is a contiguous block of memory storing elements of the same type, accessible by index in O(1) time. It is the most fundamental data structure. Dynamic arrays (JavaScript Array, C++ vector) use geometric expansion for amortized O(1) append.",
